Brighton Jones Wealth Management and Financial Advisory                       Brighton Jones  menu  We’re not just your wealth manager, we’re your Personal CFO. The decisions you make today—large and small—have a ripple effect across your future plans. Having a Personal CFO means having someone who can help you understand and anticipate the impact of those choices. Someone who will listen carefully, speak truthfully, and work proactively in pursuit of your goals. Our investment and planning expertise will help pave the path to your future, but we believe our greatest value lies in helping you live a richer life every day, starting right now.Explore these life scenarios to see what a Personal CFO can do for you.   Email us today—we'd love to hear your story.     Executive compensation We can help you make sense of—and maximize the value of—your comp package.     Complex finances Managing complicated investments, limited partnerships or multi-generational wealth requires a range of expertise.     Long-term planning “Time flies” is a cliché for a reason. Advance planning for college or retirement, or creating a succession plan, always pays off.     Liquidity event Maybe you sold a business or inherited money and you want some strategies to help make the most of it.     Life event Life is full of surprises—career change, weddings, babies, illness. It helps to have support in advance or in the moment.     A different perspective An unbiased second opinion—with no sales pitch—is critically important when the stakes are high and you’re very close to it.   Latest insights Compassion Know Your BodyDeveloping familiarization with our inner sense of self across all dimensions, emotionally, psychologically, and bodily, is essential for a sense of well-being. read more Compassion Finding Flow“The best moments in our lives are not the passive, receptive, relaxing times … The best moments usually occur if a person’s body or mind is stretched to its limits in a voluntary effort to accomplish something difficult and worthwhile.” – Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi Find Your Happy Every month this year we are highlighting simple practices that we read more Long-Term Planning 5 Reasons Why Pro Athletes Go BrokeLet’s stop pointing fingers at people and address the underlying issues.  Jed Collins of the Detroit Lions scores a touchdown against the Carolina Panthers (Grant Halverson/Getty Images) By Jed Collins After seven years in the NFL, I transitioned to a career as a financial advisor.1 The experience has afforded me a new perspective on the read more See ALL  Career Have a passion for collaboration, constant learning, and helping others succeed? Explore open opportunities at Brighton Jones. Learn more      













